note.ab:
This is the first time that Van Gogh reveals the identity of his model, Clasina (Sien, Christien) Maria Hoornik; for what is possibly the first reference to her, see letter 207. His attitude towards fallen women and his ideas about domestic and social issues and the sanctity of the nuclear family, concur with what he had read in Michelet (particularly 
                            La femme
                        ) and gleaned from English magazines. See Zemel 1987.
